The emergency may be over, but the first days at home can still feel intense. Medication timing, rest, appetite changes, and follow-up appointments all matter.

## Prepare the home before discharge

Set up a quiet recovery area, review the medication plan, and make sure you know what symptoms should trigger a call back to the hospital.

## Ask for a written plan

Families retain more when they can re-read the instructions later. Ask for written notes on feeding, activity restrictions, incision care, and emergency warning signs.

## Watch the small changes

Recovery often turns on small details: whether your dog is eating, drinking, sleeping, and moving comfortably. Track those changes early and often.
